{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Privacy — SYM.PGP.ONY{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-md-8 col-lg-7">

        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

        <section aria-labelledby="no-tracking-heading" class="mb-5">
            <h2 id="no-tracking-heading">No cookies or tracking</h2>
            <p>SYM.PGP.ONY does not use cookies, analytics scripts, session storage, or any third-party tracking technology. We do not collect information about who visits this site, how often, or from where. No data is shared with any external service.</p>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="email-usage-heading" class="mb-5">
            <h2 id="email-usage-heading">How your email address is used</h2>
            <p>When you enter your email address on the home page, it is used for two purposes only:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>To look up your PGP public key on a public key server, so that messages can be encrypted for you.</li>
                <li>To deliver the encrypted message to your inbox.</li>
            </ol>
            <p>Your email address is not stored, logged, or used for any other purpose. It is not added to any mailing list and is not shared with third parties.</p>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="token-heading" class="mb-5">
            <h2 id="token-heading">Tokenised links</h2>
            <p>The shareable link generated for you encodes your email address inside an encrypted, time-limited token. The token is encrypted using AES-256-CBC and expires after 30 days.It is not logged, and the server does not retain any record of links that have been generated or used.</p>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="no-storage-heading" class="mb-5">
            <h2 id="no-storage-heading">No server-side message storage</h2>
            <p>Messages are never stored on our servers. When a recipient submits a message through your secure link, it is encrypted in their browser before it is sent. The server forwards the encrypted message to your inbox and immediately discards it. There is no database of messages, no archive, and nothing to breach.</p>
        </section>

    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
